- ICO --> VC Funding --> 2021 bubble (firms raising funds 10-100x larger than before after early investments showed massive paper gains)  
- 2022 market crash (Luna, 3AC, FTX) caused major problems (frustrated LPs + low quality projs)  
- VC transformed from "contrarian, cash-starved, long-term thinkers" to "crowded, overcapitalized, short-term oriented"  
- 2021-2023 VC vintages will underperform because forced early selling disrupts the power-law distribution typical of VC returns  
- Dry powder (estimated at $48B in Q4 2022) has at least halved and continues declining as new fundraising stalls
